{
  "texts": [
    "Conversely, temporal dependence was addressed by introducing LSTM neural networks where the number of LSTM layers and neurons for each layer was decided through hyperparameter tuning.",
    "The network utilized a maximum pooling and dense layer to control output feature dimensionality, while a masking layer at the top handles dataset padding.",
    "The LSTM feature extractor for the classification path was trained jointly with the ANN classifier to learn the extraction of temporal features which can be used to classify component status.",
    "The number of LSTM layers to be used and the number of units for each layer were tuned using a Keras tuner to achieve optimal performance.",
    "Moreover, 5 horizon sizes were tried to see which horizon size was most appropriate."
  ]
}